Edition:
Quote: They led me along a tunnel (level, as they called it), which ran at right-angles from the main drive. At the coal-face two men were working up a ladder ... `They're blowing out tops,' Charlie explained. `Lumps of coal hanging from the ceiling are a danger to men working below'.
